   <h3>Terminology </h3>
<p></p>
<p>The Belgian FHIR profiles preferably use controlled, standard terminologies.</p>
<p>The terminologies referenced in this specification are:</p>
<ul>
<li><p>SNOMED-CT</p></li>
<li><p>Belgian-specific Code Systems and value sets</p></li>
</ul>
<p></p>
<p>  </p>
<a name="snomed"> </a>
<h2 id="snomed">SNOMED</h2>
<p>The current version of SNOMED-CT to use with FHIR profiles is the Belgian release (15-03-2020). It can be browsed here:</p>
<p><a href="https://browser.ihtsdotools.org/?perspective=full&amp;conceptId1=404684003&amp;edition=MAIN/SNOMEDCT-BE/2020-03-15&amp;release=&amp;languages=en,nl,fr">https://browser.ihtsdotools.org/?perspective=full&amp;conceptId1=404684003&amp;edition=MAIN/SNOMEDCT-BE/2020-03-15&amp;release=&amp;languages=en,nl,fr</a></p>
<p>This server has the FHIR capabilities in the endpoint <a href="https://snowstorm-fhir.snomedtools.org/fhir">https://snowstorm-fhir.snomedtools.org/fhir</a></p>
<p></p>
<p>The general SNOMED – online browser is found here: <a href="https://browser.ihtsdotools.org">https://browser.ihtsdotools.org</a></p>
<p></p>
<p>To try out the SNOMED CT server, please consult the documentation.</p>
<p>The terminologies in Belgium are governed by the <a href="https://www.health.belgium.be/language_selection?destination=terminology-center">Terminology Center</a>.</p>
<p>  </p>
